                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                },
                "html": "Giant octopuses favor shipwrecks, coral reefs, or underwater caverns as lairs, where they can take advantage of narrow confines for protection. Giant octopuses, like their smaller kin, are fond of adorning and decorating their lairs with found objects\u2014many of which, in the giant octopus\u2019s case, are also magical weapons, shields, or works of art salvaged from sunken ships or fallen adventurers."
            }
